│                                                                               │
│ ## Initial Observations ##                                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ The reproducer is already minimized. Based on my experience in debugging      │
│ these bugs, the issue is likely introduced by the *first transformation*, or  │
│ due to incorrect analysis information feeding into it.                        │
│ Here, the *first transformation* means the *first transformation point* that  │
│ modifies the IR in the pass regardless of whether it's in the                 │
│ `nary-reassociate` module or other modules.                                   │
│ #### Opt Information ####                                                     │
│                                                                               │
│ To gather more insight, I ran `opt` to inspect both the transformations and   │
│ the analysis results. Below are the command and the resulting log:            │
│                                                                               │
│ ```bash                                                                       │
│ $ bin/opt -disable-output --passes=print<scalar-evolution>,nary-reassociate   │
│ --scalar-evolution-use-expensive-range-sharpening                             │
│ --debug-only=scalar-evolution /tmp/reprod_hxg7h0ub.ll                         │
│ Printing analysis 'Scalar Evolution Analysis' for function 'pr120615':        │
│ Classifying expressions for: @pr120615                                        │
│   %0 = phi i32 [ %1, %header ], [ 0, %bb ], [ 0, %entry ]                     │
│   -->  {0,+,1}<nuw><nsw><%header> U:                                          │
│ ```                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ From this log, I identified the first transformation point as:                │
│                                                                               │
│ ```                                                                           │
│ llvm/include/llvm/IR/ValueSymbolTable.h::llvm::ValueSymbolTable::lookup()     │
│ ```                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Here is the relevant backtrace at the moment of the transformation:           │
│                                                                               │
│ ```stack                                                                      │
│ (frame 9) llvm/include/llvm/IR/ValueSymbolTable.h:81 in                       │
│ llvm::ValueSymbolTable::lookup                                                │
│ (frame 10) llvm/lib/IR/Module.cpp:171 in llvm::Module::getNamedValue          │
│ (frame 11) llvm/lib/IR/Module.cpp:229 in llvm::Module::getFunction            │
│ (frame 12) llvm/lib/IR/Intrinsics.cpp:743 in                                  │
│ llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclarationIfExists                                       │
│ (frame 13) llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp:15753 in                     │
│ llvm::ScalarEvolution::LoopGuards::collectFromBlock                           │
│ (frame 14) llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp:15356 in operator()          │
│ (frame 15) llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp:15390 in                     │
│ llvm::ScalarEvolution::LoopGuards::collectFromPHI                             │
│ (frame 16) llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp:15795 in                     │
│ llvm::ScalarEvolution::LoopGuards::collectFromBlock                           │
